         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">17/12/86. ¶  ¶ It was very kind of you, dear Dr Ramsay, to introduce Mr Bevan to me, who seems zealous for researches, and may thus also become useful for my branch of science, in New Guinea. It is al...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.12.17a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Edward Ramsay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">ML MSS.562, Letters to E. P. Ramsay 1862-91, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">17/12/86.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It was very kind of you, dear Dr Ramsay, to introduce Mr Bevan to me, who seems zealous for researches, and may thus also become useful for my branch of science, in New Guinea. It is also very good of you, to send me the specimen of a Vaccinium from the highest mountain of Hawaia.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hawai'i.</p>
               </note> This species is quite distinct from V. penduliflorum of the Hawaian Group, but it may have been described from Gustave Mann's or Dr Hillebrand's or Dr Wawra's collections; I will hunt up the litterature in this respect.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I take this opportunity to mention, that I am inclined, to found a new genus on the <name key="Claudea%20Bennettiana">Claudea Bennettiana</name>; I do not think it congeneric with C. elegans, nor does it fit well into <name key="Vanvorstia">Vanvorstia</name>.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Vanvoorstia</seg>?</p>
               </note> Some time ago I mentioned this view of mine to Agardh and to Schmitz, that I liked to dedicate the genus to the late Dr Sonder, who is so leadinly<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>leadingly?</p>
               </note> identified with the Algology of Australia, and who was for nearly 40 years my most intimate friend among Scientists in Europe,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Sonderia</seg>, attributed to M and cited as 'F. de Muell. in litter.' [in correspondence], was published in Agardh (1873-90), part 6, p. 117.</p>
               </note> his last letter written in life was to me, 3 days before his death; so the finding of Keramidia and other organs of reproduction will be all the more important.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wishing you and those dear to you a happy Christmas and joyful new year,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Claudea%20Bennettiana">Claudea Bennettiana</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Claudea%20elegans">Claudea elegans</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Vaccinium%20penduliflorum">Vaccinium penduliflorum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Vanvorstia">Vanvorstia</name>
            </p>
